     <div class="clinician-split">
       <div class="clinician-bio">
         <h2>Angelique Danza, M.S., LMFT</h2>
-        <p>Thank you for being here! My name is Angelique Danza, Licensed Marriage and Family Therapist based out of Murrieta, California. I became a therapist because I've always been drawn to understanding people—their stories, their struggles, and the ways they find strength even in the most difficult seasons of life.</p>
+        <p>Thank you for being here! My name is Angelique Danza, Licensed Marriage and Family Therapist based out of Temecula, California. I became a therapist because I've always been drawn to understanding people—their stories, their struggles, and the ways they find strength even in the most difficult seasons of life.</p>
         <p style="margin-top:1.4rem;">Over the years, both personally and professionally, I've come to deeply appreciate how complex and layered our experiences can be. Life doesn't follow a straight path, and neither does healing. One of the worst feelings is navigating life's struggles without a sense of connection, purpose, and support. My goal is to develop connections and provide support for my clients so navigating life's pivotal moments doesn't feel so isolated.</p>
         <p style="margin-top:1.4rem;">With over 10 years of providing psychotherapy, I have had the privilege of working with children, adolescents, adults, couples, and in group settings. My experience includes working with clients struggling with grief &amp; loss, anger management, relational conflicts, life transitions, identity loss, anxiety and depression, foster home dynamics, women's mental health, and PC 290 registrants focused on reducing recidivism and supporting public safety.</p>
         <p style="margin-top:1.6rem;font-size:.92rem;color:var(--text);">
